North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"Thomond, County Clare, Irland","North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Irland"},"nl":{"1267–":"1267–Overleden","1265–1329":"1265–1329","1285–1344":"1285–1344","1303–1344":"1303–1344","1267–Female":"1267–Overleden","1303":"1303","1267":"1267","1344":"1344","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","1329":"1329","Muscry, , Tir, Ireland":"Ierland","Thomond, North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"Thomond, County Clare, Ierland","North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Ierland"},"en":{"1267–":"1267–Deceased","1265–1329":"1265–1329","1285–1344":"1285–1344","1303–1344":"1303–1344","1267–Female":"1267–Deceased","1303":"1303","1267":"1267","1344":"1344","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","1329":"1329","Muscry, , Tir, Ireland":"Ireland","Thomond, North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"Thomond, County Clare, Ireland","North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"O'Kennedy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish and Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Ceannéidigh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Ceannéidigh</i>’ (from <i>ceann</i> ‘head’ + <i>éidigh</i> ‘ugly’); or from the Scottish Gaelic <b>Mac Cinnèidigh</b>, consisting of <i>mac</i> ‘son’ with an equivalent name. Compare   Canaday  ,   Cannady  ,   Cannedy  ,   Kannady  , and   Kenedy  .","History: Kennedy ancestral lands are found both in Ireland and in Scotland, where the family's medieval ancestral seat is sited on the Ayrshire coast, facing the Irish Sea. — The great-grandparents of President John Fitzgerald Kennedy (1917–63) came to North America as immigrants from Ireland in the 1840s. His paternal great-grandparents were Patrick Kennedy (1823–58), born in Dunganstown, County Wexford, Ireland, and Bridget Murphy, who was born probably in Owenduff, County Wexford, Ireland <i>c.</i> 1827; they came to Boston, MA, in 1849. His maternal great-grandparents were Thomas Fitzgerald (1823–85), who was born in Bruff, County Limerick, Ireland, and Rose Anna Cox, who was born probably in Tomregan or Kinawley, County Cavan, Ireland, <i>c.</i> 1835; they came to Boston, MA, in 1857. — An early Scottish Kennedy forebear of a quite different family was British colonial official Archibald Kennedy (1685–1763), the son of Alexander Kennedy of Craigoch, who emigrated to NY <i>c.</i> 1710."],"variants":[{"name":"Canada","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canaday   and   Canida  .","Spanish (<b>Cañada</b>): topographic name from <i>cañada</i> ‘glen, valley’."]},{"name":"Cannady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canady  ,   Cannaday  , and   Kannady  ."]},{"name":"Cannaday","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canaday  ."]},{"name":"Canedy","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Cannedy  ."]},{"name":"Cannedy","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canedy  ."]},{"name":"Canaday","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canada   and   Cannaday  ."]},{"name":"Canady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canada  ,   Canaday  , and   Kanady  ."]},{"name":"Canida","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  ."]},{"name":"Kanady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canady  ."]},{"name":"Kannady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Cannady   and   Kanady  ."]}]},{"name":"Sabina","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["name meaning ‘Sabine woman’, used occasionally in England since the 14th century. The Sabines were an ancient Italic race whose territory was early taken over by the Romans. According to tradition, the Romans made a raid on the Sabines and carried off a number of their women, but when the Sabines came for revenge the women succeeded in making peace between the two groups. The name <i>Sabina</i> was borne by three minor early Christian saints, in particular a Roman maiden martyred in about  127 ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sabina O'Kennedy was born in 1267, in Ireland. She had at least 2 daughters with Conor Conchobar OBrien."},"et":{"1267–":"1267–Surnud","1265–1329":"1265–1329","1285–1344":"1285–1344","1303–1344":"1303–1344","1267–Female":"1267–Surnud","1303":"1303","1267":"1267","1344":"1344","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","1329":"1329","Muscry, , Tir, Ireland":"Iirimaa","Thomond, North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"Thomond, County Clare, Iirimaa","North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1267–":"1267–Kuollut","1265–1329":"1265–1329","1285–1344":"1285–1344","1303–1344":"1303–1344","1267–Female":"1267–Kuollut","1303":"1303","1267":"1267","1344":"1344","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","1329":"1329","Muscry, , Tir, Ireland":"Irlanti","Thomond, North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"Thomond, County Clare, Irlanti","North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Irlanti"},"fr":{"1267–":"1267–Décédée","1265–1329":"1265–1329","1285–1344":"1285–1344","1303–1344":"1303–1344","1267–Female":"1267–Décédée","1303":"1303","1267":"1267","1344":"1344","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","1329":"1329","Muscry, , Tir, Ireland":"Irlande","Thomond, North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"Thomond, County Clare, Irlande","North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Irlande","lifeSummary":"Sabina O'Kennedy est née en 1267, à Irlande. Elle a eu au moins 2 filles avec Conor Conchobar OBrien."},"de":{"1267–":"1267–Verstorben","1265–1329":"1265–1329","1285–1344":"1285–1344","1303–1344":"1303–1344","1267–Female":"1267–Verstorben","1303":"1303","1267":"1267","1344":"1344","1265":"1265","1285":"1285","1329":"1329","Muscry, , Tir, Ireland":"Irland","Thomond, North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"Thomond, County Clare, Irland","North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Irland","lifeSumma